FBIS4-31135 "dreeu108_i_94007" FBIS-EEU-94-108 Daily Report 5 Jun 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs Use New Kinds of Weapons on Brcko Front Serbs Use New Kinds of Weapons on Brcko Front LD0506192794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 5 Jun 94 LD0506192794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpts] Enemy forces fired on the central part of the Brcko defense and the defenders' positions in [name indistinct]. [passage omitted] The aggressor is increasingly using new kinds of weapons. Today large numbers of projectiles 70 mm in diameter and 128-mm long were fired from Serb positions in Lipovac on Klade, using drum-shaped launchers installed on transporters. These weapons are manufactured in Russia. The highly destructive projectiles have built-in time fuses. [passage omitted]
